
[1]apocalypse

   APOC'ALYPSE, n. apoc'alyps. [Gr. from to disclose; and to cover.]

   Revelation; discovery; disclosure. The name of a book of the New
   Testament, containing many discoveries or predictions respecting the
   future state of Christianity, written by St. John, in Patmos, near the
   close of the first century.
